  <title translate="true">Motion-Laws and Cam-Laws</title>
  <meta name="DESCRIPTION" translate="true" value="Motion-Laws - also known as Cam-Laws - are the specification for the movement of a Motion-Part or Motion-Point. They define the Position, Velocity, Acceleration, and Jerk values. Most mechanical systems should use a Cam-Law that is continuous in Acceleration. Cam-Laws are defined with a Polynomial or a Trigonemtirc Function." />
