        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">The</text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true"> Traditional Motion-Laws</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> (also named </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Standard Motion-Laws</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">) have been used for many years in cam mechanisms for </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Rise</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Return</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> segments, usually with a Dwell segment before and after.</text></para>
